block.documentation:
The Power Subsystem supplies and manages electrical energy throughout the spacecraft, ensuring that all components have a reliable source of power. Solar Arrays generate electricity from sunlight, and the energy is stored in Batteries for use during eclipse periods when the spacecraft is not exposed to sunlight. The subsystem includes Power Conditioners to ensure the energy supplied to various components is stable and consistent.
The Power Management CSC oversees the distribution of power to each subsystem, making real-time adjustments based on demand. This subsystem includes redundancy in the form of multiple solar arrays and battery systems to ensure that the spacecraft remains operational even if one part of the power system fails.
